.Dd November 22, 2016
.Dt TD_MAP_PTH2THR 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm td_map_pth2thr
.Nd convert a pthread_t to a thread handle
.Sh LIBRARY
.Lb libpthread_dbg
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In pthread_dbg.h
.Ft int
.Fn td_thr_getname "td_proc_t *proc" "pthread_t thread" "td_thread_t **threadp"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
function converts a
.Ta POSIX
thread
.Fa thread
to a
.Xr pthread_dbg 3
specific thread passed in the
.Fa threadp
argument.
.Sh RETURN VALUES
If successful, the
.Nm
function will return
.Dv TD_ERR_OK .
Otherwise an error number will be returned to indicate failure as described in
.Xr pthread_dbg 3 .
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr pthread 3 ,
.Xr pthread_dbg 3
.Sh HISTORY
The
.Nm
function first appeared in
.Nx 2.0 .
